# Solo Qt App — Core Conventions

- Maintainer: solo developer; optimize for clarity over enterprise ceremony.
- Stack: Python 3.14+, PySide6, pytest, pytest-qt, ruff.
- Read `AGENTS.md` before structural changes.

## Naming

- Files: camelCase (`mainWindow.py`, `appConfig.py`).
- Variables, functions, methods, widget names: camelCase.
- Classes: PascalCase.
- User-visible UI text: Title Case with spaces (not camelCase).

## Layout

- Entry: `src/<app>/main.py` (thin launcher only).
- UI: `src/<app>/ui/` — widgets and dialogs only.
- Logic: `src/<app>/services/` — no Qt widget imports.
- Data: `src/<app>/models/` — plain Python types.
- Config: `src/<app>/appConfig.py`.

## Before writing code

1. Choose the correct layer (ui / services / models).
2. Prefer a new camelCase file in the right folder over growing a large file.
3. Split any file approaching 500 lines.

## Changes

- Minimal diff: do not refactor unrelated code.
- Match existing camelCase naming in the repo.
- Update `README.md` if user-visible behavior or run instructions change.
